    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-07-05T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-07-05T02:00:00-05:00" n="443"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d443">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.20 Manchuria/31: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The First Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Salisbury</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-05T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 5, 1938—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:56 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>417. Embassy’s 411, July 2, 4 p.m.<note n="8" xml:id="d443fn8">Not
                        printed.</note> Following from Mukden.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“47, July 2, 11 a.m.</p>
                    <p>Your June 29, 4 p.m. I am reliably informed that Ma Chan Shan’s command has
                        made contact with revolted troops and there is fighting <pb facs="0459"
                            n="455" xml:id="pg_455"/> going on in southwest Jehol with Chinese in
                        control of some localities, Police detachments from Mukden are reported to
                        have been sent south evidently to help maintain order behind disturbed
                        zone.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Repeated to Embassy, Hankow, Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Salisbury</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
